Human-Centered Design (HCD) means designing AI systems so they are easy to understand, useful, fair, and helpful for people who use them.

The goal is to ensure AI decisions are clear, transparent, and aligned with human needs.

1. Design for Amplified Decision-Making

This principle helps people make better decisions with AI, especially in high-risk situations (healthcare, finance, security).

AI should support humans, not replace them.

Key Aspects

Clarity
Information and explanations should be easy to understand.

Simplicity
Interfaces and outputs should not be complicated.

Usability
Systems should be easy and practical to use.

Reflexivity
Users should be able to reflect and question AI outputs.

Accountability
There should be clear responsibility for AI decisions.

2. Design for Unbiased Decision-Making

This principle ensures AI systems do not produce unfair or discriminatory outcomes.

Steps to Reduce Bias
Identify biases in datasets or models.
Design transparent systems that show how decisions are made.
Train users to recognize and correct bias.
Key Aspects

Transparency
AI decisions should be explainable.

Fairness
Systems should treat all groups equally.

Training
Decision-makers should understand AI limitations.

3. Design for Human and AI Learning

AI systems should allow both humans and AI models to improve over time.

This creates a collaborative learning environment.

Key Aspects

Cognitive Apprenticeship
Humans teach AI through examples and feedback.

Personalization
AI adapts to user needs.

User-Centered Design
Systems are built based on user behavior and needs.

Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF)

RLHF is a technique where humans guide AI learning by giving feedback on model outputs.

Instead of only using data, the model also learns from human preferences.

How it works
AI generates responses.
Humans rank or evaluate responses.
The feedback becomes a reward signal.
The model improves based on this feedback.
Benefits

• Improves AI performance
• Provides better training signals
• Increases user satisfaction

Amazon SageMaker Ground Truth

Amazon SageMaker Ground Truth is an AWS tool used to collect human feedback and label data.

It helps improve model accuracy using human-in-the-loop systems.

Features

• Data annotation
• Ranking model responses
• Classification of outputs
• Supports RLHF training

The labeled data becomes a reward model used to improve AI systems.

